<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 06 at 5:56PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Floyd,
southeastern Walker and northeastern Chattooga Counties through 630
PM EDT...
At 556 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Trion, or over
Summerville, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph and up to penny sized hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Summerville, Trion, Subligna, Suttles Mill, Berryton, Everett Springs
and Lake Marvin.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for northwestern
Georgia.</instruction>
